The estimated mean suitability presents high variation across Brazil (Figure 3 a). As expected, the southern regions present the lowest transmission potential (colder colours, p < 0.6), while the highest potential is estimated in the centre and along the northern coast (warmer colours, p > 1.0). The elevated regions of the country, running in parallel to the eastern coast, present a pattern of intermediate suitability (
P ≈ 0.8
) close to half the maximum potential presented elsewhere (
P ≈ 1.7
